00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:15,460
 So we're all inadequate, we all struggle with pride,

1040
00:41:15,460 --> 00:41:18,380
 we all wanna run somewhere and the remedy is found

1041
00:41:18,380 --> 00:41:19,860
 when we embrace this reality

1042
00:41:19,860 --> 00:41:21,700
 that we are sinners in need of a Savior

1043
00:41:21,700 --> 00:41:24,260
 and that Savior is Jesus and we run to Him, amen?

1044
00:41:24,260 --> 00:41:26,120
 Amen, let's pray.

1045
00:41:26,120 --> 00:41:34,740
 Lord, we thank you for the cross.

1046
00:41:34,740 --> 00:41:39,900
 We thank you that we can share embarrassing stories

1047
00:41:39,900 --> 00:41:44,900
 and inadequacies in our own life with one another

1048
00:41:44,900 --> 00:41:49,340
 and we're just grateful we can do that, God.

1049
00:41:49,340 --> 00:41:51,340
 We're grateful that we can confess these things to you

1050
00:41:51,340 --> 00:41:52,740
 and that you love us anyway.

1051
00:41:52,740 --> 00:41:58,700
 We're grateful, Lord, that our deepest fears of rejection

1052
00:41:58,700 --> 00:42:02,380
 are just cast aside when we come to the foot of the cross.

1053
00:42:02,380 --> 00:42:06,700
 We're grateful, Lord, stories like of this woman

1054
00:42:06,700 --> 00:42:10,220
 that our lives parallel that we can identify with

1055
00:42:10,220 --> 00:42:12,660
 and I pray that all of us here tonight

1056
00:42:12,660 --> 00:42:15,920
 will experience that same grace and mercy

1057
00:42:15,920 --> 00:42:17,060
 that that woman experienced

1058
00:42:17,060 --> 00:42:18,940
 when she fell at your feet, Jesus.

1059
00:42:20,980 --> 00:42:22,700
 And so, Lord, we just thank you for the gospel

1060
00:42:22,700 --> 00:42:25,380
 that our relationship with you is not founded on what we do

1061
00:42:25,380 --> 00:42:27,100
 but on what you did.

1062
00:42:27,100 --> 00:42:31,780
 And so, God, we worship you not because we're good.

1063
00:42:31,780 --> 00:42:36,700
 We worship you because you're good and you forgive

1064
00:42:36,700 --> 00:42:38,720
 and you are full of grace and mercy.

1065
00:42:38,720 --> 00:42:42,420
 And so, Lord, my friends tonight that are just trembling,

1066
00:42:42,420 --> 00:42:44,460
 that are afraid to tell somebody,

1067
00:42:44,460 --> 00:42:47,300
 I pray that you'll give them courage, Lord.

1068
00:42:47,300 --> 00:42:48,380
 That they'll talk to friends,

1069
00:42:48,380 --> 00:42:50,580
 that they'll talk to other followers of you.

1070
00:42:51,460 --> 00:42:53,900
 And they'll be able to experience the freedom

1071
00:42:53,900 --> 00:42:56,380
 that comes from running to the cross.

1072
00:42:56,380 --> 00:42:58,860
 And we pray all this in Jesus' name, amen.

1073
